Create a folder named k8s in your repository. Inside, create two files to define the Kubernetes Deployment and Service.

1. k8s/deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: restaurant-menu-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: restaurant-menu
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: restaurant-menu
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: restaurant-menu-container
        image: restaurant-menu:latest
        imagePullPolicy: Never # Crucial for using local Docker Desktop images without a registry
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80


2. k8s/service.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: restaurant-menu-service
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: restaurant-menu
  ports:
    - port: 80
      targetPort: 80
      nodePort: 30080


Don't forget to commit and push these new files (Dockerfile and the k8s/ folder) to your GitHub repository.
